===English translations===
{|
|-
|'''Literal'''<br>
:I recognize you by the fearsome sharpness,
:of your sword,
:I recognize you by your face
:that hastefully defines [[Greece|the land]] (i.e. the land's borders).

:From the sacred bones,
:of the [[Greeks|Hellenes]] arisen,
:and valiant again as you once were,
:hail, o hail, Liberty!<ref name="verse" />
||
'''Poetic'''<br>
:I shall always recognize you
:by the dreadful sword you hold,
:as the Earth with searching vision
:you survey with spirit bold.

:From the Greeks of old whose dying
:brought to life and spirit free,
:now with ancient valour rising
:let us hail you, oh Liberty!<ref name="verse" />
||
'''[[Rudyard Kipling]] (1918)'''<br>
:We knew thee of old,
:O, divinely restored,
:By the lights of thine eyes,
:And the light of thy Sword.

:From the graves of our slain,
:Shall thy valour prevail,
:As we greet thee again,
:Hail, Liberty! Hail!<ref name="verse" />
